== Mashed Sweet Potatoes ==

Wash and dry produce. Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{2} into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Place sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2
inches. Cover, bring to a boil, and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return sweet potatoes to #pot{}. Add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and
@butter{1%tablespoon}; mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Honey-Butter ==

While sweet potatoes cook, place @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small
microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until softened, ~{10-15%seconds}.

Stir in @honey{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{}.

== BBQ Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season lightly with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then rub all over with @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tablespoon}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per
side.

> Swap in chicken for pork. Cook until cooked through, 4-6 minutes per side.

== Lemony Broccoli ==

While pork cooks, place @broccoli{1} in a #large microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover
tightly with #plastic wrap{}; poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until tender,
~{1-2%minutes}.

> No microwave? No problem! Steam broccoli in a small pot with a splash of water
> until just tender, 2-4 minutes.

Carefully remove plastic wrap (watch out for steam!). Toss broccoli with
@lemon zest{from 1%lemon}, @butter{1/2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice,
and a big pinch of salt and pepper until coated.

== To Serve ==

Divide mashed sweet potatoes and broccoli between plates. Top mashed sweet
potatoes with pork. Dollop pork with honey butter and sprinkle with
@?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} if desired. Serve with remaining @lemon wedges{from 1%lemon} on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.